London Henry Maynard
S. my last to you was on the 16: curitt then amonghst others desired to provide
60 white manchesters bayes to be made up on, 2 packes, butt jomitted towrite
you, that they must be foulded in the north so as you do the devonshire
& swanskins bayes in london ⅓ of a yard long & made up with silh tape
neetlij & well handled, for goods well drest and ordered are halfe sold
I have non oof yd to answer so this fuither for covers to the inclosed bills
£100:- on I saae sampson due curitt & £53:10:5 att ½ uso on
piuckering & robinson for boath which please to procure the needfull
& pass to my acctt
a 21 August 1681

Monsr. salut dese tot covert vande factuer van 2 ½ laken aen
ul verkoght het welk gekeckt is met het goet van mons. de goodein eer
pack gemerck RK geaddresseert aen ul, ick wille niet twijffele ofte sal
ul tot contentament wesen in de facture stelle de 2 nortsche lakens
a 45 st noghtans mij dunck dat wij a ƒ6 st d'accort sijns vindie will dat
ick het selve niet wel minnder gevevad en kan soo referre dat aen ul

In Antwerpen 21: August
Amt de Hulter & van Homright
Messr. op 14 deser was aen ul mijnen lesten waer op geene antwoort had vernome
twelke alsoo niet is geschiet, midts occasie hebbe om het voordese gementioneert
schutsel en santen aen ul tegens maendagh toe te senden ingeslote is de reck
over de leste to vercoghte vatiens de welke soo het accort &vinden gelieft
volgen te anpotteeren

Brugge Raphael Coots
mijnh sedert den ul van 17 deser sijn, de 7 packen mijn geworden, als oock gemeng
frisaert het welke mij verwondere ul niet daer en heeft gehouden al soude u het selve
& die vande reght voor half het gelt ofte voor niet gegeven, hebbe om daer mede & ul
woort te presteeren & onse saeke goedt te maken, wantick tgeene soude te coot
comen soude mijnh. Coots, alst hem geliefde, in andere occasie konnen vergoeen
doch alles blest aen ul dircatie vereserret hope John collinier by nu sal gear
sijn thomas smith tot hull sal mijn resterende packen mede brengen
aen boort Jan simons tot london sijn geladen twee packen
MN. 39 met 14 modecolleure spaense lakens
N. 40 met 12 quartiens modecolleur lakens

London Hcnry Maynard
Sr. on the 20 curitt remitted you £153:10:5 in 2 sundry bills for my acctt, which I hope are
safe to hand, now receaved yd of 8h curitt the french demand as you may see by the nielese
wee supose they will have itt all, intrim thoseallarmes will much hinder our sales
so that one pack of spanish cloathes more will be enought till yd returne & that
I shall have seen you lett also the frises not yett be provided: I have given you
creditt for my half share in the 2 packes aboard John simands god send all safed over
wee have no news yett of collier I could wish you had the bt. silver tuck
coathes before you coming away from London att last m slaughter aggreed
with Peeters about the cloathes, they shall be sent him, & the rest
advisted when you here & so remaine, with kinde salute
the green cloathes I doubt shall be to darck not boeng beeng well observed the pedtt
prap send some where in closed 2 penne hinfes for mjuse for all mine are broahde
@ 23 ditto 1681
London ickering & Robinson
th
Sr. in answer to yd of 8: curitt as to the northrens most part are so fatt & do smell
that the press is already off there bj they are onely drest about the fiste, and
not all the cloth over & some doth the wooll rise, as if they were not drest
att all I finde fault boath in the buyer & dressers, becaused the bayer should
have bought no smelling, on stincing cloathes, butt observed that they were well
milled, & the dresser must have don what he is payd for beleave mee I imploy not r.
maijnard in northen cloathes, butt have most part from leeds my selfs dirertly &
have had this yeare above 300 northrens & though now then I finde reason of
complaints, yett never so as for them you sent for I cobleme not so much the
proffitt as the creditt in selling, because good well conditioned goods make the custome
returne the better & thought I doubt not butt you will finde yd acctt. in sale gett
the wollen manifactures beeng my trade, love to have gett in as much perfection as itt
can be had: as yett have sold butt y½ cloth, all the bayes & 12 white kersies, & shall
endeavout all I can to cleare the whole this winter. I observe what you write
